What is a Passenger Boarding Bridge?
A Passenger Boarding Bridge (PBB), also known as an air bridge or jet bridge, is an enclosed, movable connector that links an airport terminal gate directly to an aircraft, allowing passengers to board and disembark safely without exposure to outdoor conditions. Passenger boarding bridges improve airport efficiency, passenger comfort, accessibility, and aircraft turnaround performance while supporting a wide range of commercial aircraft.
Modern Passenger Boarding Bridges integrate advanced technologies including:
•	Automated Docking Systems for precise aircraft alignment
•	Electro-Mechanical Drive Systems for smooth and energy-efficient operation
•	IoT-enabled Predictive Maintenance for real-time equipment monitoring
•	Climate-Controlled Passenger Walkways for enhanced passenger comfort
•	Smart Airport Management System Integration for optimized gate operations
•	Energy-Efficient Designs supporting sustainable airport infrastructure
By improving boarding efficiency, minimizing turnaround times, enhancing passenger accessibility, and supporting next-generation aircraft operations, Passenger Boarding Bridges play a critical role in modern airport infrastructure worldwide.
